FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://127.0.0.1:5000


# Book Management API

API for managing **books, users, and reviews**.

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/api/v1/books]

### Get list of books [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "title": "Book A",
              "author": "Author A"
            }
          ],
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

### Create new book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "New Book",
          "author": "Author X"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 2,
            "title": "New Book",
            "author": "Author X"
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

## Book Detail [/api/v1/books/{book_id}]

+ Parameters
    + book_id: 1 (number, required) - ID of the book

### Get book by ID [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Book A",
            "author": "Author A"
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

+ Response 404

### Delete book [DELETE]

+ Response 204

+ Response 404

# Group Users

## Users Collection [/api/v1/users]

### Get list of users [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "username": "john",
              "email": "john@example.com"
            }
          ],
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

### Create new user [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "username": "john",
          "email": "john@example.com"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "username": "john",
            "email": "john@example.com"
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

## User Detail [/api/v1/users/{user_id}]

+ Parameters
    + user_id: 1 (number, required) - ID of the user

### Get user by ID [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "username": "john",
            "email": "john@example.com"
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

+ Response 404

### Delete user [DELETE]

+ Response 204

+ Response 404

# Group Reviews

## Reviews Collection [/api/v1/book-reviews]

### Get list of reviews [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "rating": 5,
              "comment": "Great",
              "book_id": 1,
              "user_id": 1
            }
          ],
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

### Create review [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "rating": 5,
          "comment": "Great",
          "book_id": 1,
          "user_id": 1
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "rating": 5,
            "comment": "Great",
            "book_id": 1,
            "user_id": 1
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

## Review Detail [/api/v1/book-reviews/{review_id}]

+ Parameters
    + review_id: 1 (number, required) - ID of the review

### Get review by ID [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "rating": 5,
            "comment": "Great",
            "book_id": 1,
            "user_id": 1
          },
          "meta": {
            "timestamp": "2026-01-01T12:00:00"
          }
        }

+ Response 404

### Delete review [DELETE]

+ Response 204

+ Response 404